                   of heat transport to compute a grid of loop models:
                   the effects of non-local transport on the
                   distribution of differential emission measure are
                   particularly important in the coronal part of loops
                   longer than the pressure scale height s p .We derive
                   a scaling law for λ0/L T in the corona, showing that
                   it grows exponentially with L/s p , and discuss
